# Auth Token Refresh Adds Two Round-Trips Per Request

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant API as API Gateway
    participant Auth as Auth Service
    participant DB as Database

    C->>API: GET /resource (expired token)
    API->>Auth: Validate token
    Auth-->>API: 401 token expired
    API-->>C: 401 (with refresh hint)
    C->>Auth: POST /refresh (refresh_token)
    Auth->>DB: Lookup refresh_token
    DB-->>Auth: User + scopes
    Auth-->>C: New access_token
    C->>API: GET /resource (new token)
    API->>Auth: Validate token
    Auth-->>API: 200 OK + claims
    API-->>C: 200 OK + payload
```

Source: auth flow trace from production span sampling, 2026-03-15. The expired-token
path adds one full /refresh round-trip plus one re-validation round-trip — total two
extra hops on the critical path.

Use this format for surfaces that auto-render mermaid (GitHub, GitLab, Notion,
Obsidian, recent VS Code). For surfaces that do not, use the `.html.tmpl` variant.
